The paper presents a technique for automatically generating features for data-driven program analyses. This falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) as it deals with program analysis. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of abstraction and reduction techniques, which are commonly used in programming languages (cs.PL). The technique also involves machine learning heuristics (cs.LG) and automation (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the evaluation of the approach in terms of performance and accuracy, which relates to computer security (cs.CR).
